eply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re:</span><hr size=1> I've been playing with these editors for a long time. I've never finished a game but I'm actually not half bad with the editor, I have a ridiculous amount of resources and if you need a link to some good resource sites, let me know. <br>
<br>
I've actually mostly been working on the same game, a test game with a extremely goofy plot line for a long time. I originally stopped working on it cause a virus ate half of the game and that was kinda discouraging, I started working on it again but when I upgraded my computer my new sound card played midi's like crap, again discouraging me. Now that I have an alternate computer that has my old, good midi playing sound card, I've started working on the game again. <br>
<br>
You can do alot with these editors if you're willing to put out the effort. Overall I think they are really fun to use and play with, although creating an actually good game really does require alot of effort. I've spent the last week pretty much just creating spell animations. *chuckles* Can't wait to get to the actual game programming part again, heheh... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=aeviwaveyfv>Aevi Wavey FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(2/21/04 8:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2469.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Here's my plan</span><hr size=1> This is just the bare bones of a plan. I took most of it off of Chrono Trigger.<br>
Basically, the main character Aulus comes across some type of portal that transports him into the past. He eventually figures out where he is, and what power he has.<br>
A strong being long ago destroyed the sun, the planet Veano's source of light and heat (I think I will change this part, its kind of cheesy). With the power of the Time Gates, Aulus and company will eventually stop the being that destroyed the sun.<br>
Bare bones, kind of a rip off, and very cheesy. Throw some ideas out there for me. I'd love to have some help on this too =D<br>
